event: content_block_stop
data: {"index":2,"blockType":"tool_use","finalContent":"{\"description\": \"Create a ForensicsAgent that performs deep investigation of security incidents. When it receives an incident handoff from the TriageAgent, it: 1) Queries Loki logs with targeted LogQL to find root cause patterns, 2) Examines Kubernetes pod logs for the affected services, 3) Queries the PostgreSQL database for application-level anomalies like unusual access patterns or data integrity issues, 4) Builds a timeline of events, 5) Identifies root cause and blast radius, 6) Updates the incident status with findings. The agent uses an iterative investigation loop - it may run multiple query passes before concluding. Tools needed: loki_query, loki_search_errors, loki_context, kubernetes_get_pods, kubernetes_get_logs, incident_update_status, incident_add_note, web_search for CVE lookups. Framework: LangGraph StateGraph with iterative investigation loop.\", \"framework\": \"langgraph\", \"tools\": \"loki_query,loki_search_errors,loki_context,kubernetes_get_pods,kubernetes_get_logs,incident_update_status,incident_add_note,web_search\"}","toolId":"toolu_bdrk_01RGu1pTTmZG8cMm6WE7SnUF","toolName":"design_custom_agent"}

