event: content_block_stop
data: {"index":3,"blockType":"tool_use","finalContent":"{\"description\": \"Create a RemediationAgent that executes automated fixes for security incidents based on ForensicsAgent findings. It: 1) Reads the investigation report and recommended remediation, 2) For P2-P4 incidents, auto-executes predefined runbooks (restart deployments, scale services, rotate secrets), 3) For P1 incidents, requires human approval before executing, 4) Verifies the fix by checking system health post-remediation, 5) Links the executed runbook to the incident, 6) Resolves or escalates the incident based on outcome. Tools needed: runbook_quick_diagnostics, incident_resolve, incident_escalate, incident_link_runbook, incident_close, kubernetes_restart, kubernetes_scale. Framework: LangGraph StateGraph with human-in-the-loop interrupt for P1 incidents.\", \"framework\": \"langgraph\", \"tools\": \"runbook_quick_diagnostics,incident_resolve,incident_escalate,incident_link_runbook,incident_close,kubernetes_restart,kubernetes_scale\"}","toolId":"toolu_bdrk_012AqS59Ry4KPFCzn6i6qYa7","toolName":"design_custom_agent"}

